<HEADLINE> Taliban Allow Iran to Collect Bodies of Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Taliban
authorities Saturday said it will allow an Iranian aircraft to
land in northern Afghanistan to collect the bodies of nine Iranian
diplomats killed there last month, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Eleven Iranian diplomats and one reporter went missing when
the Taliban took over the northern city of Mazar-e-Sharif,
stronghold of the opposition Northern Alliance.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban, who have been denying Iran's allegations of
abducting these diplomats, announced Wednesday that it had
recovered the bodies of nine diplomats. The whereabouts of the
other two diplomats and the reporter remain unknown.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban had originally said it would hand the bodies over
to the International Red Cross. But after Pakistan interceded,
they agreed to let Iran send its own aircraft to northern
Mazar-e-Sharif to collect the bodies, the reports quoted a Taliban
spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Iran has vowed to avenge the death of its diplomats and has
announced a second major military exercise on its border with
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban blamed the death of the Iranian diplomats on
renegade Taliban soldiers, warning Iran against military action
against Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"We have sent thousands of soldiers to Herat (in western
Afghanistan). We are not worried about Iran," the Taliban
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
