<HEADLINE> Some 50 Protesters Arrested in Azerbaijan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of riot policemen
clashed with opposition protesters in Baku, capital of Azerbaijan,
on Saturday, arresting at least 50 people.
</P>
<P>
The police confronted the demonstrators rallying outside the
headquarters of the Popular Front, a major opposition party, and
used batons to disperse them, Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately clear if any demonstrators were injured.
</P>
<P>
News reports from Baku said about 600 people participated in
the rally despite a government ban, and about 500 police were
deployed to stop it.
</P>
<P>
The protesters were calling for delay of the presidential
election scheduled for October 11. Opposition leaders are
boycotting the election, saying the government has too much
control over the Central Election Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
