<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil, China Qualify for Women's Volleyball GP Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Two-time World Grand Prix
champion Brazil upset world and Olympic champion Cuba while
defending World Grand Prix champion Russia downed host China in
the semi-finals on Saturday to qualify for the final of the World
Women's Volleyball Grand Prix Finals at the Hong Kong Coliseum
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil defeated Cuba 16-5, 17-16, 11-15, 17-15 for the final
berth while Russia won over China 4-15, 15-11, 15-13, 10-15,
15-13.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will take on Russia for the championship title while
China is to face Cuba in the third-place play-off in the 560,000
U.S. dollar tournament.
</P>
<P>
Lowly-fancied Brazilians made a flying start by taking the
first two sets, to the surprise of the hot-favored Cubans. The
Olympic champions from the Caribbean island state collected
themselves together to win the following set.
</P>
<P>
But a relaxed and vigorous game brought the South Americans to
a final-set victory with a narrow margin of two points and the
triumph of the match.
</P>
<P>
It was a hard battle for the Chinese as they took on taller
Russians in their semi-final encounter. Encouraged by deafening
cheers from the partisan crowd, the Chinese won the opening set
15-13. But that was followed by a two-set slam by the Russians.
</P>
<P>
Although the Chinese managed to win one set back in the
following contest, the successful blocking by their opponents
proved to be fatal. The spiking Chinese lost the decisive set
after leveling the score 11-11.
</P>
<P>
Chinese head coach Lang Ping praised her opponents for their
fierce spikes and tight defense, which she said caused her side's
defeat. The new members of the Chinese side needed more time to
gain international experience. "Experience proves to be crucial at
decisive moments," she said.
</P>
<P>
"I'm satisfied though with my players' performance today. They
have been tested in a very tough game and they did a good job,"
she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
