<HEADLINE> Abducted Italian Nun Released in Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGAIDISHU, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian nun Sister Marsa
was released late Saturday afternoon after three days of
captivity by the Somali gunmen in south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The release came after intensified efforts of the prestigious
traditional leaders in the area.
</P>
<P>
According to sources close to the elders, the release has been
unconditional based on humanitarian grounds. Previously,
unconfirmed report said that those unidentified gunmen were
demanding a ransom of 240,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Saturday nine out of the 12 abductors surrendered to
the Eyr subclan leaders after serious discussions and threats
inside the house where the nun was held in Hamar Ja-Jab district
of south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, no force was used against the abductors despite
the presence of over 10 battle wagons in the area and the fact
that the abductors had fired upon the release campaigners for
several times.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the last three militiamen holding
the nun surrendered at about 6:00 p.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
A convoy of nine battle wagons escorting the nun to her
residence in SOS ho3pital have passed through the main street of
the capital letting the people to know of the nun's release.
</P>
<P>
However, it not known what measures the elders are going to
take against the abductors who held Sister Marsa for the past
three days.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, it is not known how the dispute which brought about
the abduction of the nun will be settled since there is no word
as yet from the regional headquarters of SOS-International in
Nairobi and AbduLlahi Erro, the replaced administrator here in
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The release of Sister Marsa is a relief for many Somalis since
her abduction has brought about the total closure of Mogadishu's
main maternity and child heath care SOS hospital which offered
free medical service to hundreds of women and children every day.
</P>
<P>
The abduction of Sister Marsa has totally been different from
previous ones because the politicians, women and children all
sympathized with the humanitarian activities of the nun. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
