<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Government to Continue Existing Policies, Simitis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis stressed here Saturday that the existing policies carried
out by the Greek government would continue.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting of the National Council of Panhellenic
Socialist Movement (PASOK), Simitis said that these policies
included the continuation of the economic and developmental
policies and restructuring of the state, continuation of the
existing foreign affairs policies, accomplishing the aim of a
better quality of life for all Greeks and the development of new
social state with policies aimed to specific social groups.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the great goal for Greece was to join the
European Economic and Monetary Union (EMU) in January 2001.
</P>
<P>
As for the upcoming local elections in October, the premier
said that it would have a multiple importance toward the
strengthening of the new institutions of the local administration.
</P>
<P>
He added that there was a wide ranging program of support, the
establishment of financial independence for local governments and
the safeguarding of the employees in local administrations.
</P>
</TEXT>
