<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 17:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Allied Militia Denies Plan to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli allied South Lebanon
Army (SLA) denied on Saturday that the latest security measures
applied in the southern town of Jezzine under its control are
intended to expand the Israeli occupied "security zone."
</P>
<P>
In a statement quoted by the state-run National News Agency,
SLA's leader Antoine Lahd said that things haven't changed,
especially for Jezzine which was and will be outside the Israeli
"security zone."
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the self-styled security zone in parts of south
Lebanon in 1985 to protect its north from cross-border attacks by
Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has been waging a
guerrilla war trying to oust some 1,000 Israeli soldiers and
3,000 SLA militiamen from the country.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Lahd imposed tight security measures on Jezzine,
which lies just north of the "security zone" and policed by SLA,
asking local residents to acquire permit from an SLA barrack in
the town to leave or return to the city which has a population of
35,000.
</P>
<P>
According to his order, incoming and outgoing cars must also be
subjected to the thorough search at the Bater and Kafar Falous
crossing that links Jezzine with the rest of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lahd said the measures are designed to maintain the security of
the predominantly Christian town which has always been targeted
by Hezbollah's bombing attacks.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three months, many SLA militiamen were killed by
Hezbollah guerrillas roadside bombs in Jezzine in which civilians
were also wounded.
</P>
<P>
Lahd's decision, which will come into force from October 1,
has provoked widespread concern and condemnation across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese President Elias Hrawi feared that the tightening of
the SLA grip on Jezzine may be part of a plot to expand the
Israeli occupied border strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
