<HEADLINE> Palestinian Organizations Condemn Killing of Hamas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Several Palestinian
organizations Saturday condemned the killing of two members of the
Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) by the Israeli troops, the
Voice of Palestine (VOP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Imad Awadallah and his brother were shot to death by Israeli
troops Thursday night in Nablus, triggering widespread anti-Israel
protests throughout the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli side said the two brothers were members of the
Hamas and were responsible for the bombing incidents in Jerusalem
last year.
</P>
<P>
In a statement of condemnation, the Palestinan Independent
Commission for Citizen's Rights demanded that Israeli leaders be
indicted as war criminals and be brought before the international
criminal tribunal.
</P>
<P>
The Law Society of Palestine said in a press release that the
incident was Israel's state-sponsored assassination. It also
criticized Israel for its closure of the Palestinian territories
follwing the killing, saying the Israeli government must be
responsible for the deteriorating situation in this region.
</P>
<P>
While asking the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to
protect the Palestinian people, the organization also requested
the PNA to investigate and release all the details of the killing
incident.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian Human Rights Monitoring Group said in a
statement that the killing incident was a political one.
</P>
<P>
"The time of the killing when the U.S. Administration is
trying to revive the peace process raises doubts about the
seriousness of the Israeli government in rescuing the peace
process," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, residents from various West Bank cities took to
the streets to protest against the killing incident and over 60
Palestinians were injured during clashes with Israeli troops and
police, VOP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
