<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Senior Police Officer Dies of Heart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The chief of
Tanzania's Nine-Nine Police Department, Superintendent Ramadhani
Waziri, who is responsible for dealing with urgent affairs, has
suddenly died of heart attack at the age of 49 years.
</P>
<P>
Waziri started complaining about heart pains when he was
having dinner with his family on Friday night. He was then
rushed to a hospital in Dar es Salaam for medical treatment but
died on the way, Acting Regional Police Commander Buka Kibonda
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The body of the deceased was transported to his home village
of Madizini in the central region of Morogoro for burial
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Waziri is survived by a widow and five children. 
