<HEADLINE> Bank of China Aids Flood-Hit Hubei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) has
lent approximately one billion yuan to central China's Hubei
Province to help with the latter's flood relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
BOC President Wang Xuebing and Hubei Governor Jiang Zhuping
attended the signing ceremony for the loan.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which consists of 450 million yuan RMB and 60 million
US dollars, is earmarked for the expansion of the province's
telecommunications capacity and construction of a giant highway
bridge over the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
This is the first loan Hubei province has obtained from any
state-owned bank following this year's flood, as well as the
largest single loan the province has ever obtained. 
</P>
