<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Dalian
Wanda need just another win in the remaining five rounds of
matches to clinch the title of the Chinese First Division Soccer
League.
</P>
<P>
The defending champions domonstrated their superiority in the
Chinese soccer league by trouncing Sichuan Quanxing 6-1 at home.
It was their 16th win of the season and the victory gave them
three more points for a total of 51.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua, the closest rivals of Dalian Wanda, were
forced to a goalless draw at the hands of Shenzhen Ping'an. They
have garnered 38 points, 13 points behind the league leaders.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an overcame their recent bad form and came back to
winning track after beating Wuhan Hongjinlong 2-1 at home. The
victory earned them the third place in the league standings with
34 poings.
</P>
<P>
At Yanbian, Jilin Province, Yanbian Ao'dong played a
high-spirited game, beating the visiting Chinese Army team 5-0
for their 8th victory of the season. The victory further pulled
them away from the relegation zone.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Songri also took their home advantage to clinch a
crucial win, beating Shenyang Haishi 2-0 to place fourth in the
standings with 33 points.
</P>
<P>
In other actions on Sunday, Shandong Taishan beat Guangzhou
Apollo 2-0, Qingdao Hainiu beat Vanguards Huandao 1-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
