<HEADLINE> U.N. to Help Retrieve Bodies of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is to
help Iran retrieve bodies of the Iranian diplomats killed by
the Afghan Taliban militia, Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference with visiting Turkish
Foreign Minister Ismail Cem, Kharrazi said that the bodies of
the Iranians would be transferred by a U.N. plane from
Afghanistan to Mashhad, northeastern Iran on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that the Taliban militia agreed with
the dispatch of an Iranian plane to Mazari Sharif, northern
Afghanistan, to receive the bodies of nine Iranian diplomats
and a reporter of the official news agency IRNA killed in
the city.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban announced on Thursday that they found the
bodies of nine of the 11 missing Iranian diplomats. Iran
later confirmed the death of the nine diplomats and the
reporter, but said that two others escaped the Taliban's
massacre.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that he and Cem discussed the latest development
in Afghanistan and voiced grave concern of Tehran and Ankara over
the situation in that country.
</P>
<P>
He said that Cem delivered a message from Turkish President
Suleyman Demirel to Iranian President Mohammad Khatami. But he
did not reveal the content of the message.
</P>
<P>
Cem, who arrived Saturday night, said that the two sides
expressed their own views about Afghanistan during the
talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
