<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 14:30 GMT, September 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The Islamic Taliban militia Sunday claimed that
they had captured the central Afghan city of Bamyan, forcing the
Shiite Hezb-e-Wahdat leaders and fighters to flee towards
mountains. (Pakistan-Afghanistan-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- A total of 19,956 people had been killed in
militancy-related violence in India-held Kashmir between January
1990 and August 1998, an official report said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 40,031 militancy-related incidents had taken place
during the period, of which 7,567 were of explosions and 4,708
were of arson. (India-Kashmir-Toll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Majlis Speaker Nateq Nouri on Sunday
reiterated that Iran reserves the right to punish the crime
committed the Afghan Taliban militia, calling on international
community to appropriately deal with the group.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem,
Nouri termed the Taliban's killing of nine Iranian diplomats and a
reporter in Afghanistan as a clear aggression.
(Iran--Turkey-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- The Bangladeshi government is determined to
maintain steady supply of food to the people in any circumstances
as it has adequate food grains to meet the post-flood demand in
the country, said an official handout reaching here Sunday.
(Bangladesh-Food Supply)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A severe conflict between Azerbaijani policemen and
the opposition in Baku, capital of Azerbaijan, occourred on
Saturday, injuring dozens of people.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency quoted the Baku Police Department as
reporting from Baku on Sunday that 15 organizers of a rally were
arrested and charged with breaching public order. (Azerbaijan-Clash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian Foreign Minister Abdul Ilah al-Khatib on
Sunday condemned the killing of nine Iranian diplomats in
Afghanistan, the official Petra news agency reported.
(Jordan-Iran-Condemnation) 
