<HEADLINE> Tianjin Economic Development Area Attracts Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The economic development zone
in this north China port city has attracted nearly 800 million US
dollars in foreign investment so far this year, a rare feat for
any such zone in view of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Economic Development Area (TEDA) has altogether
drawn more than 10 billion US dollars in foreign funds, topping
all the development zones in the country, according to statistics
from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
So far, 3,040 companies are operating in the 33-sq-km TEDA, 171
of which have an average investment of over 10 million US dollars
each.
</P>
<P>
Motorola, Samsung and other electronics and telecommunications
companies, pharmaceuticals companies and machinery manufacturers
are the backbones of the TEDA, contributing 83.2 percent of the
TEDA's total industrial output value, according to the TEDA
management committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
