Azerbaijan Fazil Mustafayev, over 70 protesters were injured,
among whom some were seriously injured, meanwhile 20
demonstrators were arrested.
</P>
<P>
The opposition organization, Musavat party, said about 100
people were injured, and 15 opposition activists were arrested.
</P>
<P>
Among those arrested was Panakh Jusseinov, a key opposition
leader, former prime minister and one of ex-president Abulfaz
Elchibey's closest allies, who led the government under Elchibey
between 1992 and 1993. 
