have denied reports that they are ready to challenge BSkyB and
launch a 700m takover bid for Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Telegraph claimed that Smith Barney held talks with
United's financial advisers, HSBC holdings, but a spokesman for
the bankers said: "Salomon Smith Barney is not lodging a
counter-bid for Manchester United." 
