<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier on Post-Flood Reconstruction (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The felling of natural forests on the upper and middle reaches
of the Yangtze and Yellow rivers must be brought to a complete
halt, starting right now, to improve the ecology and reduce water
erosion, Zhu ordered.
</P>
<P>
"We must work hard for many years to come to reinforce
the major embankments of the Yangtze and Yellow rivers, remove
barriers in the rivers, and dredge the river courses, and thereby
improve our capacity to prevent and control floods," he said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to harness the Tongting and Poyang
lakes, China's two largest lakes, while the practice of reclaiming
land from lakes must be discontinued, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, the effort to resume production should also
be combined with measures to expand domestic demand, increase
investment and accelerate infrastructure construction to promote
economic development.
</P>
<P>
"We should take advantage of the reconstruction drive to
effectively readjust the industrial structure," Zhu said, but he
warned that the operation of loss-making industrial enterprises
with unmarketable products and low efficiency must not be
resumed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
