<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis Speaker Nateq
Nouri on Sunday reiterated that Iran reserves the right to punish
the crime committed the Afghan Taliban militia, calling on
international community to appropriately deal with the group.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem,
Nouri termed the Taliban's killing of nine Iranian diplomats
and a reporter in Afghanistan as a clear aggression.
</P>
<P>
The problem of genocide is not merely limited to Afghanistan
but is a crime against the entire humanity, the official news
agency IRNA quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
Nouri stressed that those responsible for the genocide should
be punished as war criminals.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official also expressed concern over Ankara-Tel
Aviv cooperation, hoping that Turkey would pay due attention to
the sensitivities of Muslim states and its neighbors regarding
its cooperation with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Cem, who arrived here Saturday evening, condemned the Taliban's
crime and expressed concern over the genocide by the Taliban in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He said that Turkey is aware of the sensitivity of the Islamic
countries, including Iran, towards Ankara-Tel Aviv cooperation and
assures them that the cooperation is not against any third
country.
</P>
<P>
Cem on Sunday also discussed the Afghan issue with his Iranian
counterpart Kamal Kharrazi, stating that Afghanistan has become a
factor of insecurity, horror and instability in the region.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that various Afghan groups should be encouraged to
hold negotiations to solve the Afghan crisis.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that Iran's policies on Afghanistan are based
on non-interference in internal affairs of the country, making
efforts to settle disputes peacefully, and encouraging belligerent
afghan groups to hold talks on formation of a national
reconciliation government.
</P>
<P>
He said interference of certain countries in the affairs of
Afghanistan and their arming of the Taliban as well as rendering
political and financial support to the group are the factors
further complicating the crisis and resulting in mass murder of
innocent people in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the siege of Bamyan, the center for Shiite Muslims
in northern Afghanistan by the Taliban, he warned against an
imminent massacre by the Taliban in that region and voiced Iran's
deep concern over the emergence of another tragedy in Bamyan.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran would continue its diplomatic efforts to prevent
mass murder in Afghanistan. 
</P>
