<HEADLINE> Shenyang-Dandong Expressway Section Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of part of the
Shenyang-Dandong Expressway, a major expressway in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, has been approved and will start next
year, according to an official source.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Benxi-Dandong section, 133.5 km long, is
expected to cost 5.48 billion yuan (660 million US dollars), an
official of the Dandong transportation bureau said.
</P>
<P>
He added that construction of the Shenyang-Benxi section of the
expressway has already been completed.
</P>
<P>
Dandong is China's largest border city and the northernmost
city on the coastline of the Chinese mainland. The expressway is
expected to enhance communications between Dandong and Shenyang,
the largest economic, transportation and cultural center in
northeast China, as well as between Dandong and Benxi, a major
industrial city.  
</P>
