<HEADLINE> Shenzhen's Contracted Overseas Investment Soars 76.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- This special economic zone
in south China's Guangdong Province reported more than 1.89
billion US dollars in contracted overseas investment in the first
eight months of this year, a jump of 76.3 percent over the same
period of last year, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate is unprecedented in recent years, and this
indicates that more and more overseas investors have confidence in
Shenzhen's investment environment and development prospects, a
city official said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Shenzhen approved a total of 1,409
overseas-funded projects in the January-August period, an increase
of 26.3 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Contracted investment from Asian countries that have been
severely hit by the still lingering financial crisis, including
Japan, Thailand, Singapore and the Republic of Korea, and from
Germany, the United States, Britain and the Netherlands has
increased significantly this year, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 284 overseas-funded enterprises have also
increased their investment in Shenzhen, he said.  
</P>
