self-control and calm, saying that holding those qualities
is a contribution to the whole nation at the key historic moment.
</P>
<P>
Meidani meantime condemned the killing was an "atrocity should
be blamed by all people, all political parties, organizations and
government offices." He also required the government and relevant
offices to find out the killer as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the opposition Democratic Party Sali Berisha Sunday
morning asked Prime Minister Fatos Nano to resign within 24
hours, or "Nano and his group will encounter unexpected results".
</P>
<P>
Berisha said that at a press conference which was held after
the urgent meeting of the party's presidium on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
After the conference, people gathering near the party's head
office poured into the Premier Residence and the Interior
Ministry and threw stones. Fierce gunshots could be heard in both
sites. Somebody had cast grenades and dark smoke was rising over
the Premier Residence. A few people were sent to hospital.
</P>
<P>
Azem Hajdari, vice chairman of Albania's Democratic Party and
chairman of the Parliamental Defense Commission, was gunned down
in front of his party's head office on Saturday night. The
assasination has heightened the tensions in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
