<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing Plans Airport Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Jiangbei International
Airport in this youngest municipality in southwest China is to
undergo a 190 million-yuan expansion soon.
</P>
<P>
Under the expansion project, scheduled for completion by the
year 2000, passenger handling capacity of the airport will be
increased from the current 2.4 million to eight million a year. By
then, it will be able to handle 24 planes per hour at peak times.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing was made China's fourth municipality in June last
year, because of its increasingly important role in economic
development, and scientific and cultural exchanges as well as in
transportation in the southwestern region.
</P>
<P>
Jiangbei Airport was built in 1990. It can accommodate A300
passenger airbuses and Boeing 747s. Its expansion is of
significant importance for Chongqing's economic development.
</P>
<P>
The expansion fund will come from central and local government
financing as well as loans from the State Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The new facilities will include a runway measuring 2,800 m by
44 m, six D-grade and two C-grade parking lots, and anti-lightning
and fire-fighting equipment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
