<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Lyne Bessette
won the women's 92-kilometer cycling road race at the
Commonwealth Games here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bessette, a former track and field athlete, beat Susy Pryde of
New Zealand by one bicycle length for a winning time of 2 hours
24 minutes and 59 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Pryde took the silver medal, followed by Anna Wilson of
Australia in the third place, all at the same time with Bessette.
</P>
<P>
Bessette, 23, is in her first year on Canada's national
cycling team. She had been a middle distance runner for 11 years
before taking up cycling two years ago. 
