<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Foreign Trade Expands at Slow Pace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 13 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province exported 49.95 billion US dollars-worth of goods during
the January-August period of this year, an increase of 8.1 percent
over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In August the province exported 6.37 billion US dollars-worth
of goods, a rise of 1.5 percent as compared to the same month in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Local foreign trade officials said that the province is
witnessing its slowest growth in exports this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Guangdong's imports are also showing signs of
slowing down; in the past eight months, the province's imports
were valued at 34.96 billion US dollars, 3.4 percent more than in
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In August, the province's imports, standing at 4.36 billion US
dollars-worth, grew by only 0.3 percent compared to the same month
in 1997. 
</P>
