<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Virtually Takes Women's Title at Pentathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Hosts China secured the
women's team title after three days' competitions in the CISM
46th Military Pentathlon World Championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With the grenade throwing and cross-country events remaining,
the Chinese women athletes have accumulated 9,883.8 points in the
three previous events, leading second-placed Denmark with an
almost unbeatable lead of 309.3 points. Sweden were a distant
third on 9,401.3 points.
</P>
<P>
As for the individual part, four-time champion Wang Lianying
of China retained her lead after clocking 28.1 seconds to claim
victory in the day's obstacles swimming.
</P>
<P>
The winning time was just 0.2 seconds behind the world record
set by her former teammate Shao Wenfang in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"It's a disappointment that she did not break the world
record," Wang's coach Wu Jianzhu said. "But now we're more
confident of winning both the team and the individual titles."
</P>
<P>
Wang, with 3,372.8 points, is now leading a Chinese 1-2-3
placings in the women's competitions. Her teammates Wu Jinfeng
and Shen Liping came on second and third with 3,275.9 and 3,235,1
points respectively.
</P>
<P>
With men's team title contest a two-horse race between China
and Brazil, the hosts, after the day's victory in the swimming
pool, maintained the top position and increased the lead over
their main rival to 238.8 points.
</P>
<P>
Though the obstacles swimming title went to Belgian Davy Van
De Cloot, China's Li Zhong still led the men's overall standings
with 3,382.9 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
