<HEADLINE> Flood Reconstruction, Anti-Smuggling Efforts Boost Shanghai's Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The huge demand for
reconstruction in the flood-ravaged regions in central China and
the country's anti-smuggling drive have boosted the industrial
performance of this dynamic economic powerhouse in east China.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's industrial output value in the first eight months of
this year totaled 378 billion yuan, up nine percent on an annual
basis, according to newly-released statistics.
</P>
<P>
Huang Qifan, director of the Shanghai Municipal Economic
Commission, said that the result was better than expected.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increase to soaring demand for textiles and
electrical appliances in the flood-relief work, and an intensified
campaign to crack down on smuggling, which poses a threat
especially to Shanghai's TV set, telecom, computer, petrochemical,
medical and tobacco industries.
</P>
<P>
The country's mammoth infrastructure financing also provides a
golden opportunity for the municipality's industrial sector to
compete in the domestic market, Huang said.
</P>
<P>
During the first eight months, industries in Shanghai
assimilated more than 2.4 billion US dollars of foreign
investment. The total amount for the whole year is expected to
reach 3.5-3.6 billion US dollars, accounting for about 75 percent
of the municipality's foreign capital utilization, compared with
2.5 billion US dollars projected for the whole year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
