<HEADLINE> GE Seeks Investment Opportunities In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- General Electric of the
United States is seeking investment opportunities in China with
the help of the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
A GE delegation led by Vice-President and Asia-Pacific
President Goran S. Malm arrived in this capital of Northeast
China's Liaoning Province Saturday, after visiting north China's
Shanxi Province and northwestern Shaanxi Province, and Beijing and
Shanghai cities.
</P>
<P>
GE Vice-President Malm said that GE has concentrated its
business activities mainly in Beijing, Shanghai and other big
cities, resulting in an insufficient understanding of Shenyang and
other important cities.
</P>
<P>
He said their trip was aimed at making up for their lack of
understanding of these cities, and in the hope of locating new
business development opportunities.
</P>
<P>
To his delight, Malm said, Shenyang and the whole of Liaoning
Province have very sound industrial infrastructures and a huge
market, creating the possibility that GE can cooperate in
many fields with Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
GE currently has 24 joint ventures or solely-funded companies
in China, employing more than 7,000 people. Its total investment
in China exceeds one billion US dollars.  
</P>
