Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. Middle East peace coordinator Dennis Ross is due in
Cairo Sunday to brief Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on the
outcome of his talks with the Palestinian and Israeli officials
over the past four days to reactivate the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa is to start a series of
talks Monday with a number of his Arab counterparts to coordinate
Arab stance toward regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
The ministers are coming to Cairo to attend the meetings of the
110th session of the Arab League Ministerial Council.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Moussa said Saturday that talks between Egyptian and French
officials will be held Monday to discuss steps to be taken to put
into force the Egyptian-French initiative on the Mideast peace
drive.
</P>
<P>
The initiative, calling for an international conference to
revive the stalled Mideast peace process, was raised in May when
Mubarak visited Paris.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- An Egyptian plane carrying 30 tonnes of relief aid to
victims of the recent floods that engulfed southern Sudan arrived
in Khartoum Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year civil war and consequent famines have claimed 1.5
million lives in the poverty-ridden African country. 
</P>
