<HEADLINE> 1stld Writethru: Senior Iranian Official Escapes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Head of Iran's Foundation for
the Oppressed and Disabled Mohsen Rafiqdoust on Sunday escaped an
assassination attempt.
</P>
<P>
Unknown gunmen opened fire on him from the hill overlooking
his office at the headquarters of the foundation on the Modarres
highway, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Rafiqdoust has received "no serious injuries," the report
said. No one has claimed responsibility for the shooting.
</P>
<P>
This followed the assassination last month of former chief
prosecutor Assadollah Lajevardi by member of the opposition
Mujaheddin Khalq Organization, which held him responsible for the
killing of many of its activists in the early 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
