<HEADLINE> PKK Stops Ceasefire with Turkish Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) leader Abdullah Ocalan has withdrawn a
unilateral truce declaration he made two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the London-based pro-PKK MED-TV Sunday,
Ocalan said "they (Turkish soldiers) did not abide by the truce we
declared. We have developed new war tactics, and we will intensify
out attacks."
</P>
<P>
"I offered a truce, but did not get a serious answer. Those who
have lost everything have nothing more to lose. I would fight to
the last rather than lead a dishonorable life," the PKK leader
added.
</P>
<P>
The government has rejected Ocalan's offer for a ceasefire as
of September 1, saying Ankara will never negotiate with the PKK.
</P>
<P>
The PKK, formed in April 1979 and declared illegal following a
1980 military coup, has been fighting since 1984 for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey, home to half of
the 10 million Kurds in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Over 20,000 PKK members have been killed since Turkish
government declared a state of emergency in southeastern Turkey in
1987.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has accused Syria, among other countries, of providing
support for the PKK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980913.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Bessette Wins Women's 92-kilometer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Lyne Bessette
edged Susy Pryde of New Zealand to take the gold medal of the
Commonwealth Games 92-kilometer cylcing road race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Anna Wilson had the race under control but
finished third after her left foot appeared to slip off the pedal
in the final sprint.
</P>
<P>
All three clocked in 2 hours, 24 minutes, 59 seconds over
roads left slippery by a light rain.
</P>
<P>
"It was a great race," said Bessette, who converted from track
and field to cycling two years ago. "I feel wonderful. It's a
great start for the Olympics."
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Bessette, in her first year on Canada's
national team, had been a middle distance runner for 11 years
before starting her cycling career.
</P>
<P>
Pryde just missed winning New Zealand's 100th gold medal in
Commonwealth Games history.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980913.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Wins 3rd at Women's Volleyball GP Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Two-time Olympic champion
Cuba defeated host China three sets to one to take third place at
the World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix Finals at the Hong Kong
Coliseum Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Cubans, whose previous Grand Prix Finals victory came five
years ago, won the third-place play-off 3-15, 15-8, 15-9, 15-7.
They had been the runners-up for the last two years.
</P>
<P>
Two-time Granf Prix champion Brazil, who upset Cuba Saturday
to qualify for the final, are to play defending champion Russia
for the champonship title later on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
