<HEADLINE> Cuba Win 3rd Place at Women's Volleyball Grand Prix Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Two-time Olympic champions
Cuba defeated hosts China three sets to one to take third place at
the World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix Finals at the Hong Kong
Coliseum here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Cubans, whose previous Grand Prix Finals victory came five
years ago, won the third-place play-off 3-15, 15-8, 15-9, 15-7.
They had been the runners-up for the last two years.
</P>
<P>
Two-time Grand Prix champions Brazil, who upset Cuba to qualify
for the final on Saturday, are to play defending champions Russia
for the championship title later on Sunday. 
</P>
