<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Bank of Agriculture and Agricultural
Cooperatives of Thailand will issue shares worth 1.5 billion baht
(37.5 million U.S. dollars) next month to boost capital, the
Bangkok Post newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting Ennoo Suesuwan, executive vice-president of the bank,
the newspaper said the shares sold to the public will be an
instrument for the bank to increase its lending capability, in
addition to capitalization efforts by the government.
</P>
<P>
The shares will be sold in packages of one ordinary share and
four preferred shares, which can be sold back to the bank after
five years. (Thailand-Bank-Shares)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- China's telecommunications market is likely to
remain immune to Asia's financial turmoil and keep fast growth
this year, thanks to increased infrastructure spending, vibrant
domestic demand and limited dependence on Asian economy, reported
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance announced a bond issue worth 100
billion yuan earlier this month to fund infrastructure
construction. It did not specified how much of the capital will go
to telecommunications but said total investment for the sector
will more than double the figure set earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry (MII) said that even the
previous investment projection represented a rise of 20 percent
over last year. (China-Telecom Industry)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- A spokesman for the Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation said Saturday the strict
regulations by the United States on Chinese wood packaging are
"irrational" and severely hinder normal Sino-U.S. trade and
bilateral economic cooperation, especially China's exports to the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that China has expressed a deep concern
about the regulations signed by the U.S. Secretary of Agriculture
on Friday, and reserves the right to further reactions.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that China opposes trade protectionism of various
forms, the spokesman expressed hope that the United States would
consider the regulations prudently, and that quarantine
departments and experts of both sides would conduct sincere and
effective cooperation in seeking a proper settlement to safeguard
the general situation of the development of bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Sino-U.S. trade in recent years has
grown rapidly and the two countries have become important trade
partners. (China-U.S.-Trade-Spokesman)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- After an increase of 5.4 percent from April to
June, the first quarter of India's fiscal year 1998-99, the
country's industrial growth fell sharply in July to 1.7 percent
from 8.2 percent the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Data released Friday by the Central Statistical Organization
(CSO) showed that industrial growth in the first four months from
April to July of the current year has slipped to 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector, which accounts for three-fourths of
the latest estimate of the Index of Industrial Production, grew by
 3.7 percent during the April to July period as compared to a 5.6
percent growth achieved a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The sector only increased by 1.2 percent in July against 8.5
percent in the same month last year while it grew by 5.5 percent
in the first quarter of the fiscal year. (India-Industrial
Growth) 
</P>
