<HEADLINE> Hundred Kilograms of Cocaine Seized in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan Judicial Technical
Police agents seized 100 kilograms of cocaine in the Turmero and
Maracay districts, according to the local press Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The drug was seized early Friday after weeks of searching
in Santa Cruz, Turmero, and some villages in the state of Sucre.
</P>
<P>
The antidrug agents arrested a National Guard's retired
lieutenant, Jumy Esparza, wanted since 1992, and detained four
workers in Aragua.
</P>
<P>
The seizure revealed a very tricky way of smuggling drug inside
frozen chickens, press reports said.
</P>
<P>
Agents have also investigated another abattoir, from which they
presume have come out several cocaine cargoes, all for Africa and
Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
