<HEADLINE> NATO Holds Military Maneuver in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- NATO started a military
maneuver in Macedonia Saturday to show its military strength, news
reports from Macedonia's capital Skopje said.
</P>
<P>
The move, coded Best Cooperative Effort 98, aims at
intervention in conflicts under the U.N. resolutions. As many as
1,500 soldiers from 13 NATO members including the United State and
13 NATO countries of peaceful partnership including Albania take
part in the three-stage maneuver.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day manoeuvre will feature air strikes and air
transportation of humanitarian relief.
</P>
<P>
This is the second military exercise held by NATO within one
month in a country bordering on Kosovo, with the first, held in
Albania in August.
</P>
<P>
Wesley Clark, European Supreme Allied Commander, said at the
opning ceremony the manoeuvre has nothing to do with the Kosovo
situation, though the whole world is paying close attention to
that area.
</P>
<P>
Maneuver spokesman Simon Macdowell said NATO is considering
plans, including military ones, to resolve the Kosovo issue, but
noting the manoeuvre is not linked with the matter.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian Defense Minister Lazar Kitanovski said the exercise
is very important for his country, because it shows NATO's
attention to his country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
