<HEADLINE> China Drafting Measures to Ensure Sustainable Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The government is considering
measures to ensure a sustainable development of agriculture in
China, "Business Weekly" reported.
</P>
<P>
The cream of the country's traditional agro-technology will be
combined with new environmentally friendly agricultural technology
in establishing an agro-tech network that saves energy and
protects the environment, the newspaper quoted an official from
the Ministry of Agriculture as saying.
</P>
<P>
Ecological agriculture will be developed mainly in the upper
and middle reaches of the Yellow and Yangtze rivers, the windy and
dusty regions in the northern parts of the country. And efforts
will also be stepped up to protect agricultural resources by
legislative means, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture Ministry and other concerned government
departments will draft and implement the State Regulations on
Comprehensive Administration of Agriculture Resources.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is also drafting the Agricultural Action Plan for
the China 21st Century Agenda, which includes a series of
environmental projects to ensure a sustainable development of
agriculture in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is also engaged in implementing regulations to protect
arable land, about 80 percent of which will be permanently
reserved for farming.
</P>
<P>
The official said that a tough task for the ministry is to
instill awareness about sustainable development among China's
population of farmers.
</P>
<P>
Though China has made much progress in achieving a sustainable
development of agriculture, it needs to make greater efforts in
this regard, challenged by such problems as growing population,
shrinking resources, worsening pollution and soil erosion, said
the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
