<HEADLINE> Klim Places Fifth in 100 Butterfly Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September13 (Xinhua) -- Michael Klim,
Australia's world champion and record holder swam a fifth fastest
qualifier in the men's 100-meter butterfly heats at the
Commonwealth Games Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Klim, winner of seven medals at last January's Perth world
championships including four golds, clocked 54.14 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Another Australian Geoff Huegill was fastest qualifier into
Sunday night's final with 53.34 seconds ahead of Pine (53.51secs)
and English hope James Hickman (53.55 secs).
</P>
<P>
Klim, who was relegated to second place behind teammate Ian
Thorpe in his 200m freestyle world championship event on
Saturday, has the year's best time of 52.25secs.
</P>
<P>
"I haven't swum a 100 Fly at an international event for three
years, so it was good to have a hit out this morning," Pine was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Hopefully, I can go 52 secs tonight, there probably will be
only three of four of us under 53, so I think about 52.5 will
about the best it's going to be to win tonight."
</P>
<P>
Huegill, now the gold medal favorite, has the year's fourth
best time of 52.90secs and was happy with his hitout. 
</P>
