<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Builds Welfare Center for Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a welfare
center for the elderly in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, has been completed at the cost of 25 million
yuan (three million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Association for Respecting the Elderly
constructed the center with funding provided by the general
public. The center is the nation's first facility of its kind
providing comprehensive services mainly for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
The center, which will provide homes for 600-700 of Guangzhou's
850,000 elderly citizens, is the city's largest non-profit welfare
facility. More that 50 elderly citizens have already applied for
quarters in the facility which will open on October 28. 
