<HEADLINE> Zannini Wins Paris-Brussels Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Stefano Zannini won the 256
kilometers Paris-Brussels classic cycling race on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Zannini, riding for the Mapei-Bricobi team, finished ahead of
compatriots Silvio Martinello and Michele Bartoli.
</P>
<P>
After riding almost the last 40 kilometers of the race in a
tight bunch with Martinello, Bartoli and France's Emmanuel
Magnien, Zannini broke clear in the final kilometres.
</P>
<P>
Martinello tried to follow, but was unable to outpace Zanino.
</P>
<P>
Bartoli followed third, and Magnien finished fourth. 
</P>
