<HEADLINE> Schwer Beats Frenchman to Retain Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Billy Schwer
retained his European lightweight title here on Saturday by
beating Frenchman Manuel Fernandes in the seventh round of a
scheduled 12-round contest.
</P>
<P>
Schwer's aggression and greater variety of blows finally told
against the plucky challenger who finished with blood pouring
from his right ear.
</P>
<P>
Fernandes had a brief spell of success in round four when he
closed Schwer down, pushing him back on his heels with hooks to
the head. But the contest turned dramatically in Schwer's favor
in the next round when he hurt his opponent with a tremendous
punch which landed on the ear.
</P>
<P>
Fernandes, under relentless pressure, turned away and dropped
his hands in surrender midway through the seventh round and the
referee called it off.
</P>
<P>
It was Schwer's 36th win in 39 contests, and he is clearly in
the running for a world title chance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
