<HEADLINE> Two Persons Die in Violent Demonstrations in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Two persons died and 77 were
injured Friday in demonstrations on the 25th anniversary of the
1973 military coup in Santiago, a Chilean police head said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Uniformed Police Director Colonel Sergio Apablaza said
356 were detained during the Friday violent demonstrations that
lasted until Saturday on the outskirts of Santiago.
</P>
<P>
He said that 18 official vehicles, traffic lights and
electricity lines were damaged and two buildings were attacked.
</P>
<P>
Vice Interior Minister Belisario Velasco said that the violent
actions showed that the security measures implemented by the
government were fully justified.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-five years ago, the Chilean government failed to obtain
a congressional majority in the elections and encountered a
deteriorating economic situation as well as an intensification of
opposition to its policies. Accelerated inflation led to food
shortages and repeated clashes between pro- and anti-government
activists.
</P>
<P>
The armed forces intervened in September 1973 and President
Salvador Allende was killed in the coup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
