<DOCNO> XIE19980913.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Establish More Nature Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial center, plans to establish three new
large nature reserves and a number of smaller reserves covering
over 40,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The three larger reserves will include polders along the
eastern shores of Chongming Island which are home to more than
2 million cranes, swallows and ducks.
</P>
<P>
A reserve covering 27,000 hectares set for the Yangtze River
estuary will provide a protected habitat for both Chinese and
white sturgeon.
</P>
<P>
The last of the larger reserves on the Beigan Mountain will
provide a home for some 10,000 egret.
</P>
<P>
Smaller reserves will be established around Dianshan Lake, on
Taiyang Island and in East Sea polder areas. All projects are
scheduled for completion by the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's three existing nature reserves cover some 700
hectares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
