<HEADLINE> Natural Gas Discovered in Indonesia's Irian Jaya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Large natural gas reserves
were discovered in Bintuni Bay, Manokrawi regency in Indonesia's
Irian Jaya province, Antara News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The latest result of a survey of the reserves shows that the
reserves reach 15 trillion cubic feet, large than those in other
countries in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from ARCO, one of the American oil
companies operating in Irian Jaya, the natural gas reserves would
soon be exploited enabling Manokwari to export liquefied natural
gas next year at the latest.
</P>
<P>
ARCO has already started making preparations including a
technical survey for the construction of the necessary
exploitation facilities and socio-cultural research on
acceptability of the local population with regard to the
developments taking place in the area, the report said.
</P>
<P>
No only will it become the largest natural gas producer in
Indonesia, Manokwari is also rich in marine, plantation, forestry
and mineral resources, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
