<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, September 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A day after the release of Independent Counsel
Kenneth Starr's report, the White House fought back Saturday with
a second rebuttal attacking each of the prosecutor's allegations
and said his arguments were focused on sex.
</P>
<P>
While saying Clinton's actions were wrong, his lawyers said
"such acts do not even approach the Constitutional test of
impeachment -- treason, bribery or other high crimes and
misdemeanors."
</P>
<P>
"After impaneling grand juries and leasing office space in
three jurisdictions and investigating virtually every aspect of
the president's business, financial, political, official and
ultimately, personal life, the Office of Independent Counsel has
presented to the House a referral that no prosecutor would present
to any jury," the White House said. (BC-US-Rebuttal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's Supreme Council of National Security (SCNS) on
Saturday decided to strengthen its forces along the border with
Afghanistan in order to prevent possible challenge by the Afghan
Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
The SCNS made the decision in a meeting presided over by
President Mohammad Khatami and with participation of senior
political and military officials in the wake of the confirmation
of the killing of nine Iranian diplomats in Afghanistan, Tehran
radio reported.
</P>
<P>
An official close to the meeting said that the deployment was
aimed at protecting Iran's territorial integrity and preventing
any possible challenge by the Taliban along Iran's border with
Afghanistan. (Iran-Troop Deployment-Afghanistan)
</P>
<P>
