JERUSALEM -- Several Palestinian organizations Saturday
condemned the killing of two members of the Islamic Resistance
Movement (Hamas) by the Israeli troops, the Voice of Palestine
(VOP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Imad Awadallah and his brother were shot to death by Israeli
troops Thursday night in Nablus, triggering widespread anti-Israel
protests throughout the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli side said the two brothers were members of the
Hamas and were responsible for the bombing incidents in Jerusalem
last year.
</P>
<P>
In a statement of condemnation, the Palestinan Independent
Commission for Citizen's Rights demanded that Israeli leaders be
indicted as war criminals and be brought before the international
criminal tribunal. (Palestinians-Condemn-Killing)
</P>
